WEBVTT

00:00.066 --> 00:10.100
Take your Bibles, please, and turn to Isaiah, chapter nine, Isaiah, chapter nine, and verse six, you may have received a little outline if you'd like to follow that tonight.

00:10.341 --> 00:21.717
Isaiah nine is our text, and we're gonna go back 700 years before the birth of our Lord and study one of the prophecies about Jesus Christ coming.

00:22.318 --> 00:28.306
One of the reasons that I believe the Bible to be the inerrant, infallible Word of God,

00:28.578 --> 00:33.303
is because of all of the prophecies that were made and then fulfilled.

00:33.924 --> 00:34.805
And you think about it.

00:35.486 --> 00:39.090
Jesus even prophesied His own death, barrel, and resurrection.

00:40.171 --> 00:50.562
And I'm amazed when you consider all of the evidences that we find concerning who Jesus is and what He has accomplished for us.

00:50.643 --> 00:52.044
And so let's stand together.

00:52.104 --> 00:53.746
Some folks are still coming in.

00:53.922 --> 00:57.788
If you need a nursery tonight, ushers, be sure to help folks with that.

00:57.828 --> 01:00.672
We have some great nursery service out across the way.

01:00.692 --> 01:04.678
We're not gonna be long tonight, but you're welcome to take advantage of that also.

01:05.760 --> 01:07.662
Isaiah is our text tonight.

01:08.684 --> 01:12.229
Isaiah chapter nine and verse number six.

01:13.050 --> 01:19.280
And we're going to read this verse, an amazing prophecy concerning the coming of Jesus Christ.

01:20.001 --> 01:23.506
And familiar to us, but let's follow it tonight.

01:23.618 --> 01:29.006
and let's learn what we can from Isaiah chapter 9 verses 6 and 7.

01:30.448 --> 01:53.522
For unto us a child is born unto us a son is given and the government shall be upon his shoulder and his name shall be called wonderful counselor the mighty God the everlasting father the prince of peace of the increase of his government and peace

01:53.890 --> 02:08.526
there shall be no end upon the throne of David and upon his kingdom to order it, and to establish it with judgment and with justice from henceforth, even forever, the zeal of the Lord of hosts will perform this."

02:09.007 --> 02:09.728
Let's pray together.

02:10.308 --> 02:22.802
Lord, thank you for this special evening, and Father, we pray that as we hear one more song, and then as we look to this scripture, that you would touch every heart tonight, Lord,

02:23.362 --> 02:36.223
and that we would be mindful of who you are and why you came, that we would see the purpose in this season, and that we would receive the message, most of all is my prayer, in Jesus' name, amen.

02:36.243 --> 02:36.924
You may be seated.

02:37.966 --> 02:41.932
Well, it seems every family has a little bit of a different Christmas schedule.

02:42.313 --> 02:44.456
How many of you will open presence tonight?

02:44.496 --> 02:49.164
Let me say, how many of you are wanting this sermon to go fast because you're opening presence tonight?

02:49.184 --> 02:50.546
Let me see where you are.

02:50.658 --> 02:58.927
All right, I used to criticize people who opened presents on Christmas Eve, but our family opened them yesterday, so everyone does it a little differently.

02:59.027 --> 03:04.273
We've got our sons go to the in-laws on Christmas, so we got to grab Christmas while we can.

03:04.753 --> 03:09.799
And how many of you are traditional Sunday morning, or Christmas morning rather, open up the presents?

03:09.819 --> 03:11.080
Let me see where you are, all right?

03:11.200 --> 03:12.161
Good, wonderful.

03:12.702 --> 03:14.263
And how many of you are Baja Humbug?

03:14.283 --> 03:15.104
You're not even known.

03:15.224 --> 03:16.786
We don't want to go there tonight.

03:16.866 --> 03:27.082
But it's such a blessing to get together and to be able to give and perhaps receive and then to rejoice over what has been given to us.

03:27.423 --> 03:37.298
And it was a lot of fun for us yesterday for a couple of different reasons, but one of the things that I enjoy about getting with our family for a few hours is just kind of

03:37.442 --> 03:41.970
listening to the children and seeing how they're growing and what they're learning.

03:42.050 --> 03:48.522
And I was reading the Christmas story yesterday morning to our grandchildren.

03:48.742 --> 03:55.314
And one of them, after I talked about Jesus, the Savior of the world, raised up her hand and said,

03:55.458 --> 03:57.020
When can I get saved?

03:57.501 --> 04:04.529
And she's getting real close, you know, she wants to be saved and understanding the gospel and getting ready.

04:05.030 --> 04:05.831
And what a blessing.

04:05.871 --> 04:11.898
Another blessing was just being around our brand new born grandbaby, little Quinn here.

04:11.958 --> 04:15.323
She's such a blessing and so quiet all during the day.

04:15.423 --> 04:23.052
So unlike her father, Larry, I'm telling you, it's amazing, but just enjoy being around the children.

04:23.613 --> 04:24.594
And when we think of

04:24.706 --> 04:35.661
Christmas, we think of children, but most of all we think of a very special baby that was born 2000 years ago, the little baby, the Lord Jesus Christ.

04:36.562 --> 04:45.754
And it's very easy in the midst of this season to kind of rush past what took place in Bethlehem 2000 years ago.

04:45.794 --> 04:51.922
Heard of a young family that was heading off on a trip for Christmas and the car was packed

04:52.002 --> 04:55.646
They had stopped the mail, stopped the newspaper delivering.

04:56.046 --> 04:59.249
They had a neighbor to keep an eye on the house and feed the dog.

04:59.289 --> 05:04.534
They had gifts for their parents, their grandparents, their aunts, their uncles, everything loaded in the car.

05:04.615 --> 05:06.056
They had plenty of antifreeze.

05:06.116 --> 05:08.398
They had their suitcases all loaded.

05:08.478 --> 05:15.565
They were in the driveway ready to pull out of the driveway when suddenly the wife said, honey, we forgot the baby.

05:18.228 --> 05:20.210
Now, some of you have done that, I'm afraid.

05:21.026 --> 05:26.936
And it's easy to do, but it should not be that way when it comes to the baby, the Lord Jesus Christ.

05:27.698 --> 05:36.614
And oftentimes we get the packages, we map out everything on GPS, we have the schedule, we have the plan, but we forget the baby.

05:37.255 --> 05:40.941
And we forget the reason that brings us together tonight.

05:40.981 --> 05:45.970
And so I want to speak to you for a few moments about this baby, the Lord Jesus Christ.

05:46.370 --> 05:52.798
I want you to think about him from Isaiah nine and six, this amazing prophecy that we read a moment ago.

05:52.838 --> 05:59.466
And the first thing I want you to think with me about tonight is the nature of this baby, the nature of this baby.

06:00.087 --> 06:04.893
The Bible says in verse number six, for unto us a child is born.

06:04.933 --> 06:05.734
Let's say that together.

06:06.095 --> 06:09.259
For unto us a child is born.

06:09.319 --> 06:15.186
Now the phrase a child is born speaks of Jesus in carnation.

06:15.618 --> 06:19.182
the fact that he became fully human.

06:19.823 --> 06:21.866
A child is born.

06:22.406 --> 06:29.195
The Bible says in 1 Timothy chapter three and verse 16, and without controversy, great is the mystery of godliness.

06:29.816 --> 06:33.060
God was manifest in the flesh.

06:33.480 --> 06:35.383
Now we've read that verse before, haven't we?

06:35.643 --> 06:37.906
But let's just say that little phrase together, shall we?

06:38.326 --> 06:41.230
God was manifest in the flesh.

06:42.031 --> 06:44.594
So the nature of this child,

06:45.186 --> 06:51.772
is given to us in the phrase, God was manifest in the flesh.

06:52.193 --> 06:53.294
God became man.

06:54.635 --> 07:01.241
Jesus, the baby in the manger, was 100% man and 100% God.

07:01.261 --> 07:03.824
As man, he never sinned.

07:04.284 --> 07:06.687
As God, he could not sin.

07:06.707 --> 07:11.371
I once read years ago, and I don't know why, but I think it was about the eighth grade.

07:11.391 --> 07:14.514
I was reading about Henry David Thoreau.

07:14.690 --> 07:29.774
and the great American poet and how he had gone one day into a pond and he got down to where the water came up covering about half of his eyes and he said, because he wanted to see the world like a frog saw the world.

07:29.954 --> 07:34.802
And I thought to myself, that is one of the weirdest things I've ever heard of anybody ever doing in their life.

07:35.490 --> 07:43.582
And he wrote some great poetry, but I don't know that you'd have to do that to really write a poem about a frog, but that's exactly what he did.

07:43.663 --> 07:46.888
He wanted to see what it might be like to be a frog.

07:47.669 --> 08:04.114
Well, Jesus Christ did not take on the form of man merely to see what it was like, but he literally wanted to identify with our sinful human race in order that he might redeem us with the blood

08:04.418 --> 08:05.359
that He would shed.

08:05.960 --> 08:16.054
The Bible tells us that He came for that very purpose, Galatians 4-5, to redeem them that were under the law, that we might receive the adoption of sons.

08:16.655 --> 08:27.410
And so we see this phrase, a child is born, and we begin to sense the nature of Jesus Christ, that this reveals His humanity

08:27.746 --> 08:32.313
But also we read in this verse this phrase which says, a son is given.

08:32.373 --> 08:38.783
Notice that in verse six, for unto us a child is born unto us a son is given.

08:39.584 --> 08:49.639
Now the term child is born refers to his humanity, but the term a son is given is a reference to his deity.

08:50.500 --> 08:54.386
Colossians chapter two and verse nine says, for in him,

08:54.530 --> 08:58.456
dwelleth all the fullness of the Godhead bodily.

08:59.057 --> 09:07.751
So the Son that was given was the Son of God, and in Him dwells all the fullness of the Godhead bodily.

09:07.791 --> 09:17.746
This is the cornerstone of the Christian faith that Jesus Christ, born of the Virgin, placed into the manger, was not just another man.

09:17.858 --> 09:20.462
but that he was fully the son of God.

09:20.642 --> 09:24.489
He was deity wrapped in humanity.

09:24.849 --> 09:40.594
The Bible says in Romans chapter 1 and verse 3, concerning his son Jesus Christ our Lord, which was made of the seed of David according to the flesh, and declared to be the son of God with power according to the spirit of holiness by the resurrection from the dead.

09:40.898 --> 09:45.165
So he was given glory, glory to God in the highest.

09:45.485 --> 09:57.023
He was given praise when he was born, but he also upon the time of his resurrection was revered as the son of God with power.

09:57.364 --> 10:03.173
And so we see in this passage, just an introduction to the nature of Jesus, who is Jesus Christ?

10:03.934 --> 10:08.882
I think the most important question a man could ever ask while living on planet Earth,

10:09.122 --> 10:10.544
Who is Jesus Christ?

10:10.624 --> 10:18.192
Because if he was the Son of God, then our entire eternal existence is dependent upon what he did.

10:18.492 --> 10:24.779
And if he was not, then it is the biggest farce that could have ever been told the story of Jesus Christ.

10:24.980 --> 10:30.486
Thank God, because he is fully God and fully man, we have hope and we have peace tonight.

10:31.206 --> 10:35.411
So we see a child is born and a son is given.

10:35.471 --> 10:38.034
This is the nature of the baby.

10:38.370 --> 10:46.051
and we're thankful tonight to worship Jesus Christ as our Lord, as the very Son of God.

10:46.512 --> 10:48.598
But I want you to see something else in this verse tonight.

10:48.658 --> 10:51.666
I want you to notice, secondly, the nobility of the baby.

10:52.098 --> 11:15.090
Now sometimes we get interested in nobility and some of you may be watching a little bit of the royal family right now and you have, it seems like a little bit of a division between the brothers and Prince Harry, he's spending his Christmas in Canada away from the family and we kind of like to watch and read about the royals and what's going on and this type of thing.

11:15.362 --> 11:18.646
But what about the nobility of the baby Jesus?

11:18.686 --> 11:19.747
What does the Bible tell us?

11:19.827 --> 11:26.135
Notice it says here in this verse, and the government shall be upon his shoulder.

11:26.836 --> 11:34.345
Now what an amazing leap from the manger to the throne, from a manger to the throne.

11:35.045 --> 11:42.194
This child born also as a son and his kingdom will come one day from the father.

11:42.626 --> 12:07.430
Now listen to what the Bible says about Jesus in Philippians 2.9, it says, where for God also have highly exalted Him and given Him a name which is above every name, that at the name of Jesus every knee should bow of things in heaven and things in earth and things under the earth and that every tongue should confess that Jesus Christ is Lord to the glory of God the Father.

12:07.470 --> 12:12.114
Now think of that, the Bible says that every tongue one day will confess

12:12.386 --> 12:20.918
that Jesus Christ, the baby that is born in the manger, is Lord, the supreme ruler of the universe.

12:20.938 --> 12:23.182
Now think about the nobility then of Jesus.

12:23.342 --> 12:24.403
We see it in a few ways.

12:24.503 --> 12:27.528
First of all, the expansion of his government.

12:27.688 --> 12:36.781
The Bible says in verse number seven, of the increase of his government and peace, there shall be no end.

12:37.402 --> 12:40.146
Now many have tried this wickedly so.

12:40.418 --> 12:42.282
to control the entire world.

12:43.024 --> 12:44.287
And yet they have failed.

12:44.587 --> 12:47.754
And yet of Jesus, it is said that of His government, there shall be no end.

12:48.035 --> 12:51.663
His kingdom will have no limits of expansion or peace.

12:52.284 --> 12:56.013
We also see the eternality of His government.

12:56.073 --> 12:58.418
For the Bible says in verse 7,

12:58.850 --> 13:09.015
There shall be no end upon the throne of David and upon his kingdom to order it and to establish it with justice from henceforth, even forever."

13:09.035 --> 13:16.594
Luke chapter 1 and verse 33 says, and he shall reign over the house of Jacob forever and of his kingdom, there shall be no end.

13:16.706 --> 13:17.747
Revelation 11, 15.

13:18.287 --> 13:30.558
And the seventh angel sounded, and there were great voices in heaven saying, the kingdoms of this world are become the kingdoms of our Lord and his Christ, and he shall reign forever and ever.

13:30.838 --> 13:33.140
How many of you love the hallelujah chorus?

13:33.200 --> 13:34.301
I love the hallelujah chorus.

13:34.862 --> 13:36.523
And our choir sang it a few weeks ago.

13:36.743 --> 13:39.626
Oh, so wonderful to hear the hallelujah chorus.

13:39.686 --> 13:43.729
And we like to stand in reverence to the Lord when we hear that song.

13:44.270 --> 13:46.692
And our favorite line is, and he shall reign

13:46.672 --> 14:16.082
forever and ever and ever and ever and I find great comfort in that because we have seen kingdoms rise and fall and we have seen leaders come and go and we see in the news about all of these different things that happen in our world today and we're told that we might receive a Christmas present from North Korea and I like our president's nickname for the president there rocket man don't you

14:17.058 --> 14:19.061
and people are wondering, what's he gonna do?

14:19.822 --> 14:33.102
And there's always these different kinds of kingdoms and all these different kinds of worries and threats, and yet there is coming a day when Jesus Christ will establish his kingdom.

14:33.883 --> 14:46.642
And of his kingdom, there will be no end, it will be expansive, it will be universal, and he will rule, just like the song says, forever and ever and ever, amen?

14:47.042 --> 14:56.498
And this is the promise that we have that one day Jesus Christ, who came the first time in the fullness of time, one day He will come the second time.

14:57.240 --> 15:02.910
And we at that time will be with Him as His children, as joint heirs with Jesus Christ.

15:03.390 --> 15:05.695
And He will rule forever and ever.

15:05.795 --> 15:07.418
And keep that in your heart and mind.

15:07.818 --> 15:09.221
I'm proud to be an American.

15:09.421 --> 15:10.343
I love America.

15:10.363 --> 15:12.306
I love the red, white and blue.

15:12.386 --> 15:18.491
Often times can become emotional thinking of the sacrifices men have made and women have made for our country.

15:18.772 --> 15:19.953
But I've got to tell you something.

15:20.033 --> 15:22.955
I have a citizenship that is not of this world.

15:23.255 --> 15:25.257
It is a heavenly citizenship.

15:25.277 --> 15:28.040
And I'm looking for my king, the Lord Jesus Christ.

15:28.060 --> 15:29.801
You say, well, why are you looking for him?

15:29.821 --> 15:34.445
Because he said so clearly in John chapter 14, I go to prepare a place for you.

15:34.485 --> 15:39.490
And if I go to prepare a place for you, I will come again that where I am, there you may be also.

15:39.730 --> 15:42.372
Hey, one day we're going to be in a kingdom with the Lord Jesus Christ.

15:42.352 --> 15:44.054
It's an eternal kingdom.

15:44.555 --> 15:55.289
And if you have accepted Christ as your Savior, then you can have that promise that you're gonna be in an eternal kingdom, a forever kingdom, the kingdom of the Lord Jesus Christ.

15:55.349 --> 15:58.253
And of his government, there shall be no end.

15:58.774 --> 16:01.377
Jesus Christ will serve no for your terms.

16:03.020 --> 16:06.384
He will rule forever and ever and ever.

16:06.845 --> 16:10.930
So we see in Isaiah 9, 6, the nature of this baby,

16:11.010 --> 16:19.262
And we see, secondly, the nobility of this baby that he will become the king to whom every one of us will bow.

16:19.682 --> 16:22.667
But notice, finally, tonight the name of this baby.

16:22.687 --> 16:29.296
Now, I like names, and it's interesting to me to watch young couples, and I guess we did it too, you know?

16:29.596 --> 16:33.342
Everything's weird when a young couple does it now, but when you were doing it, it was normal, right?

16:34.684 --> 16:39.250
It's interesting to watch a young couple going though through the name process today, because

16:39.330 --> 16:46.080
There's a lot of different computer search engines and books and baby name books and things.

16:46.100 --> 16:53.290
And every once in a while, someone will come up with a name that is newer and you search out the meaning.

16:53.911 --> 16:58.477
And we were told for nine months that our youngest son, Matthew, was gonna be a girl.

16:58.537 --> 17:00.240
Boy, were we surprised when he was a boy.

17:01.181 --> 17:04.926
And so he got named right there at the hospital, Matthew, gift from God.

17:05.767 --> 17:07.570
Names, they have a meaning, don't they?

17:07.970 --> 17:12.996
and we search them out and we pray about a name that would be fitting.

17:13.596 --> 17:16.179
Well, let's think about the names of Jesus.

17:16.360 --> 17:20.684
There's so many wonderful names of Jesus, but several of them are found right in this verse.

17:20.745 --> 17:22.306
Notice what it says in verse six.

17:22.987 --> 17:27.312
His name shall be called, what's the first word there?

17:28.373 --> 17:28.914
Wonderful.

17:29.414 --> 17:29.975
Wonderful.

17:30.836 --> 17:36.082
Job nine and verse 10, which doeth great things past finding out

17:36.162 --> 17:39.407
Yay and wonders without number.

17:40.168 --> 17:42.071
Jesus Christ is wonderful.

17:42.472 --> 17:44.815
We used to sing a song when I was a teenager growing up.

17:45.196 --> 17:48.621
Isn't he wonderful, wonderful, wonderful?

17:49.042 --> 17:51.706
Isn't Jesus my Lord, wonderful?

17:51.766 --> 17:56.233
Eyes have seen, ears have heard, it's recorded in God's word.

17:56.774 --> 18:00.260
Isn't Jesus my Lord, wonderful?

18:00.320 --> 18:01.842
And he is wonderful.

18:02.210 --> 18:03.752
Everything about him is wonderful.

18:04.092 --> 18:05.734
His attributes are amazing.

18:05.774 --> 18:06.635
He's all-knowing.

18:06.735 --> 18:08.537
He's omnipresent.

18:08.577 --> 18:14.383
The fact that Jesus Christ created the world and sustains the world.

18:14.664 --> 18:16.105
He is wonderful.

18:16.385 --> 18:17.647
He is awesome.

18:18.067 --> 18:29.560
And sometimes we see children at Christmas getting excited about maybe a Lego set from Star Wars or maybe some game that they're going to play and how awesome this superstar is and awesome this superstar is.

18:30.180 --> 18:31.602
And yesterday afternoon,

18:32.034 --> 18:35.541
Our daughter Danielle, I said, hey, find a nice Christmas show for the kids.

18:35.601 --> 18:41.133
And so she found one that said something, had something about some story and in the story was Santa Claus.

18:41.193 --> 18:43.358
And so they are watching it for about five or six minutes.

18:43.759 --> 18:47.346
It was Santa Claus as in claws, as in a monster.

18:49.090 --> 18:54.677
And I know my daughter's getting a little bit older, but I said, sweetheart, that is not a good movie.

18:55.158 --> 18:59.784
And by the way, we found a wonderful movie called Star.

18:59.964 --> 19:06.112
It's an animated film of all places produced last year by Sony and rather biblical.

19:06.452 --> 19:08.895
And I would highly recommend it if you have young children.

19:08.975 --> 19:13.021
I sat there and watched a cartoon yesterday afternoon with my grandchildren.

19:13.061 --> 19:14.162
It was wonderful.

19:14.242 --> 19:18.929
to see the Lord presented in that way in a way that the children enjoyed so much.

19:19.730 --> 19:24.657
But everything about the Lord is wonderful and His name is wonderful.

19:25.137 --> 19:28.001
And what a blessing that we serve a perfect Savior.

19:28.462 --> 19:37.815
You know, I've seen people bow and pray to statues of Buddha, but when you look closely, the statues are cracked and sometimes they're tilted.

19:38.757 --> 19:42.642
And I've seen people literally, and you have too on the news,

19:43.042 --> 19:48.767
give their very lives for their profit, and yet their profit is so far from perfect.

19:49.909 --> 19:56.835
And yet you and I tonight get to sing and give and worship a wonderful savior.

19:56.895 --> 19:57.656
Isn't that a blessing?

19:58.557 --> 20:00.919
That he is perfect in all of his attributes.

20:00.979 --> 20:02.481
He is perfect in every way.

20:03.001 --> 20:05.023
And so the name of Jesus, he's wonderful.

20:05.103 --> 20:09.027
Notice the next word it says, his name shall be called wonderful.

20:09.107 --> 20:10.088
What's the next word say?

20:11.309 --> 20:12.370
Counselor.

20:12.578 --> 20:13.239
counselor.

20:14.521 --> 20:17.406
You know, every one of us need counsel.

20:17.807 --> 20:18.848
We need good counsel.

20:19.509 --> 20:24.678
And there's no greater counsel than you can receive than the counsel from the Lord Jesus.

20:25.559 --> 20:31.669
No one is God's counselor, but he is the omniscient source of wisdom.

20:32.470 --> 20:34.674
He is the counselor

20:34.850 --> 20:40.296
Romans 11 and verse 33, oh, the depth of the riches, both of the wisdom and knowledge of God.

20:40.356 --> 20:49.867
How unsearchable are his judgments and his ways past finding out for who hath known the mind of the Lord or who hath been his counselor?

20:50.668 --> 20:54.573
You know, he didn't have to search Google to figure out how to create stars.

20:55.954 --> 21:02.642
And he didn't have to read a manual to figure out how to develop and build and create the Rocky Mountains.

21:02.914 --> 21:07.661
He didn't have to try to figure out and get counsel when it came to creating Adam.

21:07.962 --> 21:13.350
How many of you are thankful tonight that we serve a God who can give counsel in every way.

21:13.631 --> 21:18.498
His counsel is perfect and he's recorded it for us in his word.

21:18.559 --> 21:19.640
He is wonderful.

21:20.261 --> 21:21.343
He is counselor.

21:21.383 --> 21:22.925
Notice the next name now.

21:22.965 --> 21:27.052
The next name says this, that he is the mighty God.

21:27.092 --> 21:28.434
Let's say that together.

21:30.306 --> 21:34.414
Now many religions of the world today deny this truth.

21:35.837 --> 21:41.950
And folks, if we're going to be followers of Christ, then I would submit to you tonight that doctrine actually matters.

21:43.292 --> 21:44.775
What we believe really does matter.

21:45.597 --> 21:50.066
And we believe that Jesus Christ is the mighty God.

21:50.466 --> 21:58.540
You say, well, there are some people that came by my house and they passed out some brochures and they said that Jesus was the son, but he wasn't equal to the father.

21:58.861 --> 22:02.487
You know, folks, you say, pastor, why do you believe that Jesus is God in the flesh?

22:02.748 --> 22:04.872
Because the Bible says he's God in the flesh.

22:05.553 --> 22:06.955
He is the mighty God.

22:07.597 --> 22:08.859
And we think about this name.

22:09.540 --> 22:10.642
This is a title.

22:10.978 --> 22:14.083
that is given to our God, Revelation 1 and 7.

22:14.404 --> 22:23.379
Behold, he come with clouds, and every eye shall see him, and they also which pierced him, and all the kindreds of the earth shall wail because of him, even so, amen."

22:23.399 --> 22:24.781
This speaks of his second coming.

22:25.422 --> 22:30.130
I am the Alpha and Omega, the beginning and the ending saith the Lord, which is

22:30.242 --> 22:34.230
and which was and which is to come the Almighty.

22:34.311 --> 22:36.816
We serve a God that is mighty.

22:37.116 --> 22:39.241
He lives in the past, present and future.

22:39.261 --> 22:41.065
He's the Alpha and the Omega.

22:41.506 --> 22:43.570
He is the mighty God.

22:43.618 --> 22:47.163
and we worship a God that has all power.

22:47.303 --> 22:49.767
Jesus said, all power is given to me.

22:50.087 --> 22:52.410
Go ye therefore and teach all nations.

22:52.470 --> 23:00.682
And what a great truth that is tonight to know that when we pray, we're not praying to some weak old man up in heaven with a long beard and a rocking chair.

23:00.942 --> 23:04.187
We are praying to the mighty creator of the universe.

23:04.908 --> 23:06.210
He is mighty God.

23:06.290 --> 23:12.018
And I don't know what your burden is tonight, but I know this, even at Christmastime, people have burdens.

23:13.442 --> 23:21.834
In our mind might get off the burdens when we look into the face of a child or open a gift, but every one of us tonight have some burdens that are hard to carry.

23:21.855 --> 23:28.384
And I just want to tell you something tonight that you can cast your cares upon the Lord because he cares for you.

23:29.286 --> 23:31.829
And he's stronger than you and he can bear those burdens.

23:31.849 --> 23:33.852
He is a mighty God.

23:34.273 --> 23:43.026
And then notice the next one says of this baby that he is the everlasting father, the everlasting father.

23:43.618 --> 23:49.266
What an amazing phrase or name to give to a baby.

23:49.730 --> 23:53.256
Jesus came to do the will of his father and he and the father are one.

23:53.276 --> 23:54.558
In fact, Jesus taught this.

23:54.918 --> 23:59.025
He said, I and my father are one, John 14, nine.

23:59.325 --> 24:03.953
Jesus sayeth unto him, have I been so long time with you and yet you have not known me Philip?

24:04.253 --> 24:09.261
He that have sent me the father is the father and how then say is show us the father.

24:09.421 --> 24:15.531
Hebrews one and verse three, who being the brightness of his glory and the express image of his person.

24:16.512 --> 24:17.554
The story is told,

24:18.114 --> 24:21.312
of December 1903 after many, many attempts.

24:21.413 --> 24:23.122
Finally, the Wright brothers

24:23.170 --> 24:25.393
had just a little bit of flight.

24:25.453 --> 24:39.533
They had, in fact, the first flight of their flying machine that got off the ground, and they were thrilled, and they telegraphed a message to their sister, Catherine, and they said, we have actually flown 120 feet.

24:39.874 --> 24:41.576
We will be home for Christmas.

24:41.997 --> 24:46.903
And Catherine ran to the newspaper editor, and she said, you've got to have this story.

24:47.364 --> 24:48.726
And here was the story.

24:49.026 --> 24:51.570
The boys will be home for Christmas.

24:53.634 --> 24:58.542
She had totally missed the small part about the first flight of man.

25:00.124 --> 25:06.273
Folks, whatever you do this Christmas, don't miss the significance of who Jesus is.

25:07.255 --> 25:08.256
He is wonderful.

25:09.038 --> 25:10.039
He is counselor.

25:10.580 --> 25:11.842
He is mighty God.

25:12.603 --> 25:16.529
He is the everlasting Father, and then notice this finally.

25:16.970 --> 25:19.614
He is the Prince of Peace, the Prince of Peace.

25:19.854 --> 25:22.258
Our God is the peacemaker

25:22.370 --> 25:23.612
and the peace giver.

25:24.333 --> 25:34.489
The Son, Jesus, is the visible King who has promised to come through David's seed and to sit upon David's throne in kingdom, then shall peace rule the earth.

25:34.509 --> 25:43.423
The only time true peace is on the earth is when Jesus Christ comes and presents himself as King of Kings and Lord of Lords.

25:43.984 --> 25:45.426
During the first Advent,

25:45.570 --> 25:50.781
In Luke chapter 2 and verse 14, the Bible pronounced glory to God in the highest on earth peace.

25:51.302 --> 25:52.505
Good will toward men.

25:52.906 --> 25:55.952
But at his second coming, he will subdue Satan.

25:55.973 --> 25:58.257
He will bring peace to this earth.

25:58.277 --> 26:00.081
He will provide peace.

26:00.562 --> 26:02.226
And the Bible even says that

26:02.370 --> 26:09.059
There will be even amongst the animal kingdom peace on earth when Jesus Christ comes the second time.

26:09.340 --> 26:15.007
Romans 16 and 20, and the God of peace shall bruise Satan under your feet shortly.

26:15.288 --> 26:18.452
The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you.

26:18.512 --> 26:23.559
And so tonight, just take a moment to ponder and think about the baby.

26:24.240 --> 26:25.982
Think about the nature of the baby.

26:26.002 --> 26:28.806
Fully man, fully God.

26:29.627 --> 26:31.730
Think about the nobility of this baby.

26:32.226 --> 26:36.170
that of his government, there shall be no end.

26:36.931 --> 26:40.034
And think about the names of this baby, wonderful.

26:40.975 --> 26:48.983
Counselor, the mighty God, the everlasting Father, and the prince of peace.

26:50.504 --> 26:54.809
Ronald Reagan once spoke these words about Jesus.

26:56.390 --> 27:00.274
Think of a young man whose father is a carpenter

27:00.802 --> 27:03.024
He grows up working in his father's shop.

27:03.966 --> 27:05.567
He has no formal education.

27:05.607 --> 27:08.030
He owns no property of any kind.

27:08.090 --> 27:11.834
One day he puts down his tools and walks out of his father's shop.

27:11.854 --> 27:18.562
He starts preaching on street corners in a nearby countryside and walking from place to place, preaching all the while.

27:18.942 --> 27:25.810
Even though he is in no way and ordained minister, he never gets farther than in the area, perhaps 100 miles wide at most.

27:26.626 --> 27:28.068
He does this for three years.

27:28.168 --> 27:30.091
Then he is arrested, tried, and convicted.

27:30.131 --> 27:35.859
There is no court of appeal, so he is executed at the age of 33, along with two common thieves.

27:36.980 --> 27:41.346
Those in charge of his execution rolled the dice to see who would get his clothing.

27:42.368 --> 27:49.838
The only possessions he had, his family cannot afford a burial place, so he is in turn, in turn in a borrowed tomb.

27:50.619 --> 27:51.420
End of story?

27:52.101 --> 27:52.562
No.

27:52.962 --> 28:14.707
This uneducated, propertyless young man who preached on street corners for only three years, who left no written word, has for 2,000 years had a greater effect on the entire world than all the rulers, kings and emperors, all the conquerors, the generals and admirals, all the scholars, scientists and philosophers who ever lived all put together.

28:15.027 --> 28:20.914
How do we explain that unless he really was who he said he was?

28:22.274 --> 28:27.361
wonderful counselor, the mighty God, the everlasting Father, and the Prince of Peace.

28:27.421 --> 28:43.283
There is no way to explain the phenomenon, the works, the miracles, the majesty, the hundreds of millions of followers of Jesus except to know that he is God come down in the flesh.

28:44.885 --> 28:48.690
And it's one thing to see how he has changed other people's lives.

28:49.634 --> 28:56.060
to see the many hospitals that have been raised up in his name, to see the universities raised up in his name.

28:56.501 --> 29:05.749
It's one thing historically to look and to see the impact of Jesus as Ronald Reagan did, but it's another thing to have your life impacted by Jesus Christ.

29:06.851 --> 29:15.559
Because the Bible says, the wages of sin is death, but the gift of God is eternal life through Jesus Christ our Lord.

29:16.680 --> 29:18.802
And when someone receives his gift,

29:19.010 --> 29:26.861
When someone by faith accepts Jesus Christ as their savior, the Bible says, if any man is in Christ, he's a new creature.

29:26.921 --> 29:28.884
Old things are passed away.

29:29.144 --> 29:30.546
Behold, all things have become new.

29:30.586 --> 29:32.689
Now listen to that phrase, in Christ.

29:33.851 --> 29:35.353
Are you in Christ tonight?

29:36.996 --> 29:39.239
Are you in Christ tonight?

29:40.200 --> 29:41.442
Is he in you?

29:41.722 --> 29:44.306
Have you received Christ as your savior?

29:45.282 --> 29:49.886
Now, did you know that you can be in a Baptist church and not be in Christ?

29:52.009 --> 29:56.513
You can be in a religion and not be in Christ.

29:57.794 --> 30:02.138
The Bible says, therefore, if any man be in Christ, he's a new creature.

30:02.198 --> 30:06.042
Old things pass away, behold, all things become new.

30:07.123 --> 30:09.205
It's one thing to study the names of Jesus.

30:10.086 --> 30:14.130
It's another thing to receive the nature of Jesus yourself.

30:14.818 --> 30:18.564
to receive Him as your Savior and to become a new creation.

30:19.385 --> 30:21.448
And that's the gift that He brought to us.

30:22.370 --> 30:26.476
That gift wrapped in swaddling clothes 2,000 years ago.

30:27.397 --> 30:32.666
That one, to whom the shepherds bowed and to whom the wise men gave.

30:33.867 --> 30:35.190
He is still wonderful.

30:36.131 --> 30:38.354
He is still counsel or He is still mighty God.

30:38.615 --> 30:40.177
He is still the everlasting Father.

30:40.418 --> 30:43.282
And He can still bring peace to your heart.

30:43.874 --> 30:49.522
If you have never received Christ as Savior, I would encourage you to do that even tonight.

